"Teng H., Yamasaki A.","Pressure-mole fraction phase diagrams for Co2-pure water system under temperatures and pressures corresponding to ocean waters at depth to 3000 m",2002,"Chemical Engineering Communications","189","11",,"1485","1497",,,10.1080/00986440214993,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0042458363&partnerID=40&md5=c5781c7d98298ac3b7f384b4d6880933","Natl. Inst. Adv. Indust. Sci./Tech., Tsukuba 305-8569, Japan","Teng, H., Natl. Inst. Adv. Indust. Sci./Tech., Tsukuba 305-8569, Japan; Yamasaki, A., Natl. Inst. Adv. Indust. Sci./Tech., Tsukuba 305-8569, Japan","Pressure-mole fraction phase diagrams for the CO2-water system at temperatures between 278.15 and 298.15 K and pressures up to 30 MPa, which correspond to those of ocean waters at depths to 3000 m, are developed based on the literature data and experimental results obtained by the authors. The resultant phase diagrams can serve as a basis for analyzing the phase behavior of liquid CO2 and CO2 hydrate disposed of in the ocean as a means to mitigate global warming.","CO2 hydrate; CO2-water system; Global warming; Pressure-mole fraction phase diagram","Carbon dioxide; Hydrates; Pressure effects; Thermal effects; Water; Ocean waters; Phase diagrams; carbon dioxide; depth; fluid flow; global warming; ocean wave; temperature effect",,,,,,"Adisasmito, S., Frank III., R.J., Sloan Jr., E.D., (1991) J. Chem. Eng. Data, 36, p. 68; Aya, I., Yamane, K., Yamada, N., (1993) Proceedings of the International Symposium on CO2 Fixation and Efficient Utilization of Energy, pp. 351-360. , eds. Y. Tamaura, K. Okazaki, M. Tsuji and S. Hirai, Research Center for Carbon Recycling and Utilization, Tokyo Institute of Technology, Tokyo; Bozzo, A.T., Chen, H.-S., Kass, J.R., Barduhn, J., (1975) Desalination, 16, p. 303; Chun, M.-K., Yoon, J.-H., Lee, H., (1996) J. Chem. Eng. Data, 41, p. 1114; Crovetto, R., (1991) J. Phys. Chem. Ref. Data, 20, p. 575; Deaton, W.M., Frost Jr., E.M., (1946), 8. , U.S. Bureau of Mine